Areas of Research/Interest: Renaissance and Baroque art and architecture; history of prints and print culture.     Fellowships/Honors: James S. Ackerman Scholar in Residence, American Academy in Rome, 2008; J. Clawson Mills Senior Fellow, Metropolitan Museum of Art, 2006-07; Frese Senior Fellow, Center for Advanced Study in the Visual Arts, National Gallery of Art, 2000-01; Premio Salimbeni, for The Altars and Altarpieces of New St. Peter's, 1998; Andrew W. Mellon Postdoctoral Fellow, American Academy in Rome, 1994-95; summer research grant, American Philosophical Society, 1994; Premio Salvatore Rebecchini, for Specchio di Roma barocca, 1992; Samuel H. Kress Predoctoral Fellow, American Academy in Rome, 1984-86     Select Publications:   "Matthaeus Greuter and the Conclusion Industry in Seventeenth-Century Rome," in Ein privilegiertes Medium und die Bildkulturen Europas. Deutsche, Französische und Niederländische Kupferstecher und Graphikverleger in Rom von 1590 bis 1630 , ed. E. Leuschner, Rome, 2012, pp. 221-38 "Art History Reviewed, X: Francis Haskell, Patrons and Painters. A Study in the Relation between Italian Art and Society in the Age of the Baroque, London, 1963," Burlington Magazine , CLII, 2010, pp. 543-46 "Prints for Pentecost: The Title Plates and Frontispieces to an Annual Sermon in Seicento Rome," in L'Estampe au Grand Siècle. Études offertes à Maxime Préaud , ed. P. Fuhring et al., Paris, 2010, pp. 235-67 "Cardinal Rapaccioli and the Turnip-sellers of Rome: A Satire on the War of Castro by Baccio del Bianco," Master Drawings , XLVII, 2009, pp. 53-69 "Simon Vouet's Hesperus and the Mythopoetics of Praise," in Dialogues in Art History, from Mesopotamian to Modern: Readings for a New Century [Studies in the History of Art , 74], ed. E. Cropper, New Haven and London: National Gallery of Art, 2009, pp. 236-51 "Urbano VIII e il dilemma del portico del Pantheon," Bollettino d'arte , no. 143, 2008, pp. 93-110  "POMIS SUA NOMINA SERVANT: The Emblematic Thesis Prints of the Roman Seminary," Journal of the Warburg and Courtauld Institutes , LXX, 2007 (2008), pp. 195-246  "Bernini and the Pantheon Bronze," in Sankt Peter in Rom 1506-2006. Beiträge der internationalen Tagung vom 22. - 25. Februar 2006 in Bonn , eds. G. Satzinger et al., Munich: Hirmer, 2008, pp. 337-52  " Apes philosophicae : Bees and the Divine Design in Barberini Thesis Prints," in I Barberini e la cultura europea del Seicento. Atti del convegno internazionale (Roma 7-11 dicembre 2004) , eds. L. Mochi Onori et al., Rome: De Luca, 2007, pp. 181-94  "The Pentecostal Meaning of Borromini's Sant'Ivo alla Sapienza," in Francesco Borromini 1599-1667. Atti del convegno internazionale (Roma 13-15 gennaio 2000) , eds. C. L. Frommel et al., Rome and Milan: Electa, 2000, pp. 259-70  "Jesuit Thesis Prints and the Festive Academic Defence at the Collegio Romano," in The Jesuits: Cultures, Sciences, and the Arts, 1540-1773 , eds. J. O'Malley et al., Toronto: University of Toronto Press, 1999, pp. 148-69  The Altars and Altarpieces of New St. Peter's. Outfitting the Basilica , 1621-1666, New York and Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 1997  Specchio di Roma barocca. Una guida inedita del XVII secolo (with Joseph Connors), Rome: Edizioni dell' Elefante, 1991; paperback ed. 1996       Update your faculty profile

NYU > Art History > Faculty >            Meredith Martin                                                        Back to Home                   Meredith Martin   Institute of Fine Arts; Associate Professor of Art History Ph.D. 2006, M.A. 2003, Harvard University; B.A. 1997, Princeton University   Phone: 2129988293              Areas of Research/Interest: 18th- and 19th-Century French and British art, architecture, material culture, and landscape design; art and gender politics, cross-cultural encounters in European art; interiors and identity; historical revivalism and contemporary art     Fellowships/Honors: Finalist for the Berkshire Conference of Women Historians First Book Prize   The Drawing Institute at the Morgan Library and Museum Fellowship, 2012  Andrew W.
